Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), indicating possible renal dysfunction and/or urinary tract pathology. HbA1c is low, which may reflect recent hypoglycemia or anemia. No evidence of infection (negative nitrite/leukocytes). Recommend further evaluation of renal function and possible underlying metabolic or urinary tract disorders.
